EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to Medicaid; creating the Medicaid Health Care
Workforce Account; prescribing the authorized uses of
the money in the Account; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Office of Science, Innovation and Technology in the
2 Office of the Governor to establish and administer a Graduate Medical Education
3 Grant Program as a competitive grant program to award grants to institutions in this
4 State seeking to create, expand or retain certain programs for residency training for
5 physicians and postdoctoral medical fellows. (NRS 223.637) Existing law
6 authorizes the Board of Regents of the University of Nevada to administer a
7 program to provide loans for fees, books and living expenses to students in the
8 nursing programs of the Nevada System of Higher Education. (NRS 396.890)
9 Existing law authorizes the Nevada Health Service Corps established by the
10 University of Nevada School of Medicine to administer a program to repay the
11 student education loans on behalf of certain health care practitioners who practice
12 in areas of this State in which a shortage of that type of practitioner exists. (NRS
13 396.903) Section 1 of this bill creates the Medicaid Health Care Workforce
14 Account. Section 1 requires the Administrator of the Division of Health Care
15 Financing and Policy of the Department of Health and Human Services to use the
16 money in the Account to: (1) pay the costs of administering the Account; and (2)
17 support projects and programs to expand the health care workforce of this State for
18 which certain federal financial participation is available. Section 2 of this bill
19 requires the Director of the Department to administer the provisions of section 1 in
20 the same manner as other provisions relating to Medicaid.
