THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 422 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The Medicaid Health Care Workforce Account is hereby
4 created in the State General Fund. The Administrator shall
5 administer the Account.
6 2. The money in the account must be used to:
7 (a) Pay the costs of administering the Account; and
8 (b) Support projects and programs to expand the health care
9 workforce of this State for which federal financial participation is
10 available under Title XIX of the Social Security Act, which may
11 include, without limitation:
12 (1) Programs to provide graduate medical education;
13 (2) Programs to pay the indirect costs of medical education;
14 (3) Fellowship and apprenticeship programs for providers
15 of health care; and
16 (4) Programs to assist with repayment of student education
17 loans for providers of health care.
18 3. The Administrator may apply for and accept any gift,
19 donation, bequest, grant or other source of money for the purposes
20 described in subsection 2. Any money so received must be
21 deposited in the Account.
22 4. The interest and income earned on the money in the
23 Account, after deducting any applicable charges, must be credited
24 to the Account. Any money remaining in the Account at the end of
25 the fiscal year does not revert to the State General Fund, and the
26 balance in the Account must be carried forward to the next fiscal
27 year.
28 5. Claims against the Account must be paid as other claims
29 against the State are paid.
30 6. As used in this section, “indirect costs of medical
31 education” means the higher costs for patient care paid by
32 facilities that provide graduate medical education relative to
33 facilities that do not provide graduate medical education.
